I'm back at coding after five years and I'm trying to rebuild a config system. I was using derive_builder for everything before, but now I want stricter validation so I can't accidentally leave required fields out like the old days. Here is my current setup:

struct Config {
    name: String,
    port: u16,
}
impl Default for Config { ... }

fn main() {
    let c = Config::builder()
        .name("server")
        .port(8080)
        .build();
}
